# Known Issues — Third-Party Library Gotchas

Problems that cost 8+ tool calls to diagnose the first time. Read this section BEFORE debugging accessibility tree issues with any library.

## vis-timeline (v7.4.7+)

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `role`, `aria-label`, `data-testid`, `class` silently stripped from item content HTML | Built-in XSS sanitizer strips all non-whitelisted attributes | Add `xss: { disabled: true }` to Timeline constructor options. Guard with `import.meta.env.DEV` so production keeps protection. Must be set at instantiation — `setOptions()` won't work. |
| Console warning: "You disabled XSS protection for vis-Timeline" | Expected when using `xss: { disabled: true }` | Harmless in dev. Do not suppress it in production. |
| HMR doesn't reinitialize the timeline after code changes | vis-timeline creates its instance in `onMount` — HMR swaps the component but doesn't re-run `onMount` | Full page reload (`browser_reload`) after changes to Timeline options or item builders. |

## SvelteFlow / XYFlow

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Custom node components have correct `role`/`aria-label` in DOM but don't appear in `browser_snapshot` | SvelteFlow sets `visibility: hidden` on `.svelte-flow__node` wrappers during its measurement pass. `visibility: hidden` removes elements from the accessibility tree. | Add CSS: `.graph-canvas :global(.svelte-flow__node) { visibility: visible !important; }`. Safe because nodes have explicit positions from layout. |
| Node wrappers have `role="group"` and `aria-roledescription="node"` | SvelteFlow's default ARIA. Your inner `role="button"` on the custom node component works inside this — no conflict. | No fix needed. Just know it's there so you don't waste time investigating it. |

## General patterns

| Symptom | Likely cause | Diagnostic |
|---|---|---|
| Attributes added to HTML string content disappear | Library has a sanitizer (XSS, DOMPurify, or custom) | Check rendered innerHTML: `document.querySelector('.item')?.innerHTML`. If attributes are gone, search library docs/issues for "xss", "sanitize", "whitelist". |
| Element exists in DOM with correct attributes but missing from accessibility tree | CSS `visibility: hidden` or `display: none` on the element or an ancestor | Check: `getComputedStyle(el).visibility` and `getComputedStyle(el).display`. Also check: `el.closest('[aria-hidden="true"]')`. |
| Element appears in snapshot but with `nth` index instead of a name | Multiple elements share the same accessible name | Add unique `aria-label` incorporating the item's identity (e.g., `"Edit {name}"` instead of just `"Edit"`). |
| `scrollIntoView` doesn't bring element into viewport | Element is inside a nested scrollable container | Use a duplicate button in the main content area, or scroll the inner container explicitly with `browser_scroll` targeting the container ref. |
